lower bound on the\nfield size is $\\Omega(n^2)$ and the best known upper bounds are $O(n^5)$ for a\nnon-explicit construction and $O(n^{32})$ for an explicit construction. In this\npaper, we give an explicit construction over fields of size $O(n^3)$ which\ncomes very close to being optimal.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Dec 2022 18:54:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-22"}
