ase to 174 and 2794\nif one allows a low level of metal-rich contaminants. Conclusion: The inclusion\nof photometric information greatly contributes to breaking parameter\ndegeneracy, enabling precise metallicity estimates for VMP stars from Gaia RVS\nspectra. We produce a publicly-available catalog of bright metal-poor stars\nsuitable for high-resolution follow-up.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 22 Dec 2022 12:11:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-23"}
